Due to the ruling of Governor Scott to cancel all fairs and festivals this season due to COVID 19 we respectfully abide and have to postpone our 2020 Fall Festival until 2021. We look forward to seeing all of you at our wonderful event next year!

Preschool Registration: If you have a child who will be 3 or 4 by September 1st, and you are interested in registering them for the preschool, please contact Corrina Favreau at cfavreau@fwsu.org to request a registration form or if you have any questions. If you have already registered OR your child currently attends the GEMS preschool program, you do not need to register again.

The initial screening process will be done through an electronic questionnaire this year. Once all required enrollment documents are received, you will receive the screening form and questionnaires through your email account.

post_text: Library books can start being returned to GEMS tomorrow, Thursday May 28th. The return cart will be located on the top step by the main entrance Monday’s through Thursday’s from 7:00-3:00 and Friday’s 7:00-10:00. Please do NOT leave books if the return cart is not outside. If there is another family at the cart when you arrive, you will need to wait on the sidewalk until the cart is available, please remember to practice social distancing while you wait. If the provided hours do not work for your schedule, there will be more opportunity to come.

We are currently scheduling times for 5/6 locker clean outs on May 28th and 29th, and June 1st and 2nd from 10am to 2pm. Use the link below to sign up for a time.

You MUST sign up in advance for a time. Please do not show up without a scheduled time.

Only one student at a time will be allowed in the building and MUST wear a mask. Parents are to remain in their cars.

A staff member will meet students OUTSIDE the middle school entrance and will escort them to their lockers. Students will NOT be allowed in classrooms.

(7th & 8th grade locker pick up will be scheduled soon, an email will be sent to families when your child's belongings are ready for pick up)

If you have specific questions, please email Jen Follensbee at jfollensbee@fwsu.org.

https://www.ptcfast.com/schools/Georgia_Elementary_and_Middle_School_1

post_text:
Middle School Parents: Schoology is experiencing issues due to the amount of people using it, this is not an issue associated with just GEMS. If your child gets the image below, then Schoology is at capacity and is currently down, they are aware and are in the process of fixing the issue. If your child gets logged out, have them do the following to get logged back in:

Using SAFARI or Chrome (web browser):
1. Type into the address bar at the top: schoology.fwsu.org
2. You will be presented with a Google login. Enter in your FWSU email address and password.

Using the Schoology app on the iPad.
1. In the area to search for the school, type in the exact same thing as Safari: schoology.fwsu.org
2. From the list of schools, tap on Franklin West Supervisory Union
3. Tap "Log in through your School"
4. This will pull up the same Google login screen as Safari. Enter in your FWSU email address and password

Rise VT - Franklin & Grand Isle Counties
February 21 at 9:37 PM ·

To celebrate the last day of moretti’s Rise in Residence at￼ Georgia Elementary & Middle School, Mrs. Sikorsky’s class was given an adventure challenge that pushed team building limits and allowed each student to let their strength shine. Puzzle pieces were floating on lava. Students had to safely traverse the molten lake to complete a goal and then collect the puzzle pieces to assemble.
They navigated unstable noodles and frustration to solve the 3 puzzles. The cheer of accomplishment was fantastic!

shared_text:
Rise VT - Franklin & Grand Isle Counties
February 21 at 9:43 PM ·

Sometimes lakes of molten lava release toxic chemicals into the air. At least this one at Georgia Elementary & Middle School did. Unfortunately, the result was that every student lost their voice! Thy had to complete the task of rescuing the puzzle pieces and each other without a word.
They tackled that challenge with barely the bat of an eye. Mrs. Sikorsky’s class rocks!

Rise VT - Franklin & Grand Isle Counties
February 21 at 9:43 PM ·

Sometimes lakes of molten lava release toxic chemicals into the air. At least this one at Georgia Elementary & Middle School did. Unfortunately, the result was that every student lost their voice! Thy had to complete the task of rescuing the puzzle pieces and each other without a word.
They tackled that challenge with barely the bat of an eye. Mrs. Sikorsky’s class rocks!

post_text:
Preschool registration for 2020-2021!
If you have a child that will turn 3 or 4 years old before September 1st and are interested in the Georgia Preschool Program in the fall, please contact Corrina Favreau in the main office at 524-6358 or at cfavreau@fwsu.org to request a registration form. Students who currently attend the Preschool Program do not need to register again.
